  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alliance fights avoidable blindness (AFAB 2) Mali</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Mali, a rapid assessment of avoidable blindness (RAAB) survey in people over 50 in the Koulikoro region found untreated cataract to be the leading cause of blindness. The World Health Organisation&#x2019;s (WHO) Universal Eye Health Global Action Plan (GAP) 2014-2019 recommends that all member states have national plans and committees to ensure the effective delivery of eye health programmes and promote the integration of eye health into broader health systems. Currently Mali does not have a functioning national committee or an approved national plan. To address the weaknesses identified by the situational analysis the Action Plan will focus on the following areas: cataracts, refractive errors, glaucoma, diabetic retinopathy and strengthening the health system at national and regional levels.</narrative>
  </description>
